<a name='4024564607052585976'></a>
<h3 class='post-title'>
<a href='http://www.informationdissemination.net/2010/01/libya-complains.html'>Libya Complains</a>
</h3>
<div class='post-header-line-1'></div>
<div class='post-body'>
<p>Germany is suffering a <a href="http://blog.foreignpolicy.com/posts/2010/01/28/gaddafis_son_blames_germany_for_supporting_israeli_war_crimes">touch of blowback</a> for <a href="http://www.informationdissemination.net/">its naval deal with Israel.</a>  A critical letter was released by Qaddafi's son Saif al-Islam Alqadhafi, who, according to FP, is increasingly influential in shaping Libyan foreign policy.   There's no indication that the Germans plan to take this complaint seriously, although I wonder if the naval cooperation might become a major anti-German jihadist talking point.</p>
<div style='clear: both;'></div>
</div>
<div class='post-footer'>
<p class='post-footer-line post-footer-line-1'>
<span class='post-author'>
Posted by
Robert Farley
</span>
<span class='post-timestamp'>
at
<a class='timestamp-link' href='http://www.informationdissemination.net/2010/01/libya-complains.html' title='permanent link'>5:57 PM</a>
</span>
<span class='post-comment-link'>
