<h3 class='post-title'>
<a href='http://www.informationdissemination.net/2010/01/coast-guard-praise.html'>Coast Guard Praise</a>
</h3>
<div class='post-header-line-1'></div>
<div class='post-body'>
<p><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://cgvi.uscg.mil/media/main.php?g2_itemId=755416"><img style="margin: 0pt 0pt 10px 10px; float: right; cursor: pointer; width: 216px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_cys2T5FgJdo/S1ddKpbn94I/AAAAAAAAHeo/dx0n1vMfFAU/s320/Albacore_Haiti.jpg" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5428910313320216450" border="0" /></a>There is a great deal of praise for the US Coast Guard coming from...<br /><br /><a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/blog/2010/01/19/men-and-women-united-states-coast-guard">The White House Blog</a>. Well deserved in my opinion. ADM Thad Allen's blog has been updated with the <a href="http://www.uscg.mil/comdt/blog/2010/01/haitian-relief-efforts-force-laydown.asp">full list of Coast Guard forces</a> supporting operations in Haiti.<br /><br />Regular updates from the <a href="http://coastguard.dodlive.mil/">Official Coast Guard Blog</a>.<br /><br />Finally, a photo gallery <a href="http://cgvi.uscg.mil/media/main.php?g2_view=keyalbum.KeywordAlbum&amp;g2_keyword=Haiti">here</a>.</p>
<div style='clear: both;'></div>
